  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nThe `abi.ParseSelector` function creates a valid JSON encoded ABI for selector calculation, but we could go one step further and enable creating a proper ABI for `abi.ABI.Unpack` method.\r\n\r\nThis would address most cases where we want to quickly call a single method on a contract.\r\n\r\n`abi.ParseSignature(\"balanceOf(address)(uint256)\")`\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nWe could (1) simply export \r\n```golang\r\nabi.parseIdentifier\r\nabi.parseCompositeType\r\nabi.assembleArgs\r\n```\r\nfor external use.\r\n\r\nor we might (2) add a `abi.ParseSignature` function that will have this extended logic\r\n\r\nor we could just expand on the functionality of the existing `abi.ParseSelector` function in a backward compatible manner.\r\n\r\nI am very much ready to implement any of those solutions.",
